#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/processing-modules/watermark.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"marker\n"
": Choose the watermark to apply. Use the reload button to update the list to include any newly-added watermarks. The extension of the file (png/svg) is shown in brackets.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/processing-modules/watermark.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"text\n"
": A free text field in which you can enter up to 63 characters to be printed where referenced by the corresponding watermark. An example is supplied as `simple-text.svg`.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/processing-modules/watermark.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"text color\n"
": The color of the text. Click on the colored field to open a color selector dialog which offers you a choice of commonly used colors, or allows you to define a color in RGB color space.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/processing-modules/watermark.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"text font\n"
": The font to use (default \"DejaVu Sans Book\"). Click on the field to open a dialog box showing the fonts available on your system. Fonts can be searched by name and a preview is shown next to the font name. You may specify your own sample text.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/processing-modules/watermark.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"opacity\n"
": The opacity of the watermark's rendering.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/processing-modules/watermark.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"scale\n"
": The scale of the watermark, with respect to the option selected in the \"scale on\" parameter.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/processing-modules/watermark.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"rotate\n"
": The rotation angle of the watermark.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/processing-modules/watermark.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"scale on\n"
": The reference for the scale parameter. The default setting “image” scales the watermark relative to the horizontal image size. Alternatively you can scale the watermark relative to the “larger border” or “smaller border”.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/processing-modules/watermark.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
