msgstr ""

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-generate-cache.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "darktable-generate-cache"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-generate-cache.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The `darktable-generate-cache` binary updates darktable's thumbnail cache. Invoke this program to generate all missing thumbnails in the background when your computer is idle.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-generate-cache.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "`darktable-generate-cache` can be called with the following command line parameters:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-generate-cache.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"darktable-generate-cache\n"
"              [-h, --help]\n"
"              [--version]\n"
"              [--min-mip <0-8>] [-m, --max-mip <0-8>]\n"
"              [--min-imgid <N>] [--max-imgid <N>]\n"
"              [--core <darktable options>]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-generate-cache.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "All parameters are optional. If started without parameters `darktable-generate-cache` uses reasonable defaults.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-generate-cache.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`-h, --help`\n"
": Display usage information and terminate.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-generate-cache.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`--version`\n"
": Display copyright and version information and terminate.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-generate-cache.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`--min-mip <0-8>, -m, --max-mip <0-8>`\n"
": darktable can store thumbnails with up to eight different resolution steps for each image. These parameters define the maximum resolution to be generated (defaults to a range of 0-2). There is normally no need to generate all possible resolutions here -- missing ones will be automatically generated by darktable the moment they are needed. When asked to generate multiple resolutions at once, the lower-resolution images are quickly downsampled from the highest-resolution image.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-generate-cache.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`--min-imgid <N>, --max-imgid <N>`\n"
": Specifies the range of internal image IDs from the database to work on. If no range is given, `darktable-generate-cache` will process all images.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/purge_non_existing_images_sh.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "purge_non_existing_images.sh"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/purge_non_existing_images_sh.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Find and remove entries from the library database referencing images that no longer exist in the filesystem. You must close darktable before running this script.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/purge_non_existing_images_sh.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The script can be called with the following command line parameters:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/purge_non_existing_images_sh.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"purge_non_existing_images.sh [-c|--configdir <path>]\n"
"                             [-l|--library <path>]\n"
"                             [-p|--purge]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/purge_non_existing_images_sh.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Run the script with no options to perform a \"dry run\", which generates a report of the missing files without committing any changes to the database.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/purge_non_existing_images_sh.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The available options are:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/purge_non_existing_images_sh.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`-c|--configdir <path>`\n"
": Specify the path to the darktable configuration directory to be used by the script. If this option is not provided, the default config directory location will be used.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/purge_non_existing_images_sh.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`-l|--library <path>`\n"
": Specify the path to the library.db database file to be analysed by the script. If this option is not specified, the default library.db file location will be used.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/purge_non_existing_images_sh.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`-p|--purge`\n"
": Actually delete any entries in the database that refer to non-existent files. If the option is not provided, a report will be printed without committing any changes to the database.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/purge_non_existing_images_sh.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "**Notes:**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/purge_non_existing_images_sh.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The script must be run in a unix shell, and the `sqlite3` client must be available in the command search path. For Linux systems, this will normally not be an issue. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2. '
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/purge_non_existing_images_sh.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "For Windows systems, you will normally need the MSYS2 environment to be installed, as described in the [instructions for building darktable in a Windows environment](https://github.com/darktable-org/darktable/blob/master/packaging/windows/BUILD.md). If you installed darktable using the standard Windows installer package, the location of the script would normally be something like: `C:\\Program Files\\darktable\\share\\darktable\\tools\\purge_non_existing_images.sh`.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '3. '
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/purge_non_existing_images_sh.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "For macOS systems, the Terminal application provides a shell, and the `sqlite3` client is provided by the operating system by default. If darktable was installed using an application bundle from a dmg image, then the default location for the script would be `/Applications/darktable.app/Contents/Resources/share/darktable/tools/purge_non_existing_images.sh`\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '4. '
